During resources phase resources subnet is created with the same CIDR
as during setup. Ironic requires to have a route to this network from
control plane (ironic-conductor).
This patch creates a new network with has an unique CIDR and GATEWAY
defined by RESOURCES_FIXED_RANGE and RESOURCES_NETWORK_GATEWAY.

commit_message:
Update resources subnet CIDR

During resources phase resources subnet is created with the same CIDR
as during setup. Ironic requires to have a route to this network from
control plane (ironic-conductor).
This patch creates a new network with has an unique CIDR and GATEWAY
defined by RESOURCES_FIXED_RANGE and RESOURCES_NETWORK_GATEWAY.
Default value for RESOURCES_FIXED_RANGE is 10.2.0.0/24 and
for RESOURCES_NETWORK_GATEWAY is 10.2.0.1

Change-Id: I83f9f90809bbf2e6d73c7282bbb9b2be084b6a66
Co-Authored-By: vsaienko <vsaienko@mirantis.com>
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/ironic refs/changes/82/317082/16 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: RESOURCES_NETWORK_GATEWAY=${RESOURCES_NETWORK_GATEWAY:-10.2.0.1} RESOURCES_FIXED_RANGE=${RESOURCES_FIXED_RANGE:-10.2.0.0/20} NEUTRON_NET=ironic_grenade # this builds a default network for other services to use net_id=$(neutron net-create --shared $NEUTRON_NET | grep ' id ' | get_field 2) resource_save network net_id $net_id local subnet_params="" subnet_params+="--ip_version 4 " subnet_params+="--gateway $RESOURCES_NETWORK_GATEWAY " subnet_params+="--name $NEUTRON_NET " subnet_params+="$net_id $RESOURCES_FIXED_RANGE" local subnet_id subnet_id=$(neutron subnet-create $subnet_params | grep ' id ' | get_field 2) resource_save network subnet_id $subnet_id local router_id router_id=$(neutron router-create $NEUTRON_NET | grep ' id ' | get_field 2) resource_save network router_id $router_id neutron router-interface-add $NEUTRON_NET $subnet_id neutron router-gateway-set $NEUTRON_NET public # NOTE(vsaeinko) sleep is needed in order to setup route sleep 5 # Add a route to network to access instances from ironic-conductor local r_net_gateway r_net_gateway=$(sudo ip netns exec qrouter-$router_id ip -4 route get 4.2.2.1 |grep dev | awk '{print $7}') sudo ip route replace $RESOURCES_FIXED_RANGE via $r_net_gateway

commit_message:
Fix cluster attributes dns_list and ntp_list

Settings in release change. Cloned cluster should have values valid for
its release.

dns_list and net_list were text values but in version mitaka-9.0 it
changed to text_list

(cherry picked from commit 5ae4c7ebdcdbf1621ce617de4ec019ae2b5670c4)

commit_message:
Using text/plain for error responses

This prevents XSS attacks injecting scripts to error messages. Currently
http error constructor sets content-type to text/html for errors with
the code 500.

Change-Id: I21b5855ebe102060f4046706b5c6ab2e3e532162
Closes-Bug: #1583602
(cherry picked from commit 25fca4bb847bf6e16b0a0c7c35437b7a478e81b1)

commit_message:
Catch DriverLoadFailure for get_transport optional

new oslo.messaging 5.2.0 release will raise
oslo_messaging.transport.DriverLoadFailure if no existent transport
driver, hence breaks our code and unit test as well.

This patch fixes it by adding DriverLoadFailure to catch list.

Change-Id: I318d4b93beac9d1816fe4b5f9eb9de98e4debc04
Closes-Bug: #1588151
(cherry picked from commit 9c5df8400b621141db93a259900efe3702eb6241)

added_lines: except (oslo_messaging.InvalidTransportURL, oslo_messaging.DriverLoadFailure): if not optional or url:
deleted_lines: except oslo_messaging.InvalidTransportURL as e: if not optional or e.url:

commit_message:
Cancelled live migration are not in progress

Since we have introduced the new API for aborting a running live
migration we have introduced a new state called "cancelled" which is
applied to all the aborted live migration job in the libvirt driver.
This new status is not filtered by the sqlalchemy query used to get the
list of the all migration in progress for host and node.

Change-Id: I219591297f73c4bb8b1d97aaf298681c0421d1ae
Closes-bug: #1588378

commit_message:
Do not use instance.id in the name property

The ability to have an instance name rely on the 'id' field is a horrid
thing that has been allowed to continue for too long. This comes to a
head with cellsv2 work for two reasons:

1. An instance does not have an 'id' until it is in a cell db, and the
   'id' is generated by the receiving db, so it can not be used for name
   generation in the boot request response.

2. With multiple cells the 'id's will not be unique any longer. This
   means that any reliance on a monotonically increasing int in the name is
   going to break anyways. And that was never an intended feature.

In order to keep deployers from needing to change their
instance_name_template if it uses 'id' this patch simply uses the uuid
anywhere that 'id' would be used.

Change-Id: Iee5aa74c181211513ba76d2d93b58fb805bd5d6f
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/nova refs/changes/83/326083/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: import uuid def test_name_does_not_use_id(self): inst = objects.Instance(uuid=str(uuid.uuid4())) self.flags(instance_name_template='foo-%(id)s') # It's not important that uuid is used here, it's important that the # inst.name access does not fail trying to lazy-load inst.id. self.assertEqual('foo-%s' % inst.uuid, inst.name)

commit_message:
Tempest image clients use version in URL

Tempest image clients specify the version in each URL of each
method instead of using api_version at class level, which provides
support for both versioned and unversioned enpoints in the
catalog.

Change-Id: Id7883936b5a7ff13dc71fff307a5322c63221ad5
Closes-bug: #1130387

commit_message:
Minor revise cluster_update and profile_update

This patch revises cluster_update and profile_update service
call to make them raise badrequest exception when being
invoked without giving any property to be updated.
Also default cluster timeout is now specified in cluster_create
service call rather than in API layer if it is not provided
when cluster_create API is invoked. And cluster_update
actually don't need default timeout input value.

Change-Id: Ied2adfc676da4b8c4e3e89f41001f460982c39bb

commit_message:
Prevent creating kernel and ramdisk ids with 'None' value

This commit prevents convertion of None values to 'None'
strings for kernel_id and ramdisk_id, since glance v2
image schema forbids it.

The properties of images previously created as 'None' strings
are converted to None.

Co-Authored-By: Samuel Matzek <smatzek@us.ibm.com>

Change-Id: I06eef936004ae83f1805abeb422adcf9078fbc79
Closes-bug: #1539698

commit_message:
Minor revise profile_update API

The patch revises profile_update API to make it raise
BadRequest exception when user tries to update profile Spec.
This is for keeping consistent with policy_update API.

Change-Id: I8da796c7dd6f308713883af9b8889241d796bd7d

commit_message:
Fix default sort keys in v3

For non-type-versioned request we allow to sort
artifact list by available base properties only.
But current implementation is wrong because keys
from v2 are used as defaults.

This code fixes it by setting the correct set of keys.

FastTrack
ApiImpact
Closes-Bug: #1490600

Change-Id: I63d914b5e823bd5f809c3c96fac1265341646441

commit_message:
Make Xenplugin to work with glance v2 api

This code makes xenplugin version agnostic and
allows to work with both apis, depending on what
version is considered as 'current'
Plugin version is bumped to 1.4.

Related to blueprint use-glance-v2-api

Change-Id: I368d1362eb19713b0f84b940f9d25a1caf78b03b
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/nova refs/changes/33/266933/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: supported_glance_versions = (1, 2) def _determine_curr_major_version(endpoint): """Determines the current major version of the glance API in use :returns Integer version number or None if unable to determine version """ try: conn = httplib.HTTPConnection(endpoint) conn.request('GET', '/versions') resp = conn.getresponse() if resp.status != 200: return None content = resp.read() for version in content['versions']: if version['status'] == 'CURRENT': res = version['id'] # The 'id' value looks like "v2.2", # so grab the major version number which is 2 in this case res = int(res[1:res.find(".")]) return res if res in supported_glance_versions else None except Exception: logging.error("Unable to determine the glance API version") def _get_image_url(endpoint): """Returns correct image url for current glance api version""" version = _determine_curr_major_version(endpoint) if version == 1: return "%(glance_endpoint)s/v1/images/%(image_id)s" else: # In any unclear situation we use the second version. return "%(glance_endpoint)s/v2/images/%(image_id)s/file" url = (_get_image_url(glance_endpoint) % { url = _get_image_url(glance_endpoint) % {

commit_message:
Remove version hardcoding for 'create' and 'update' methods

This patch continues the big initiative to make Nova
adopt Glance v2 API. In this patch 'create' and 'update'
methods are improved to work with both versions.

Depends-On: Id0f1c398b8b48f2ffc2488b29bc7cbd279069337
Depends-On: I2bd454990d90f60b0d6505d56c9ce23836e82e3b
Related to blueprint use-glance-v2-api

Change-Id: Idcd98327480c35c4f1dbe0656b87b57df9a85ef2

commit_message:
Remove version hardcoding for 'detail', 'download' and 'delete' methods

This patch continues the big initiative to make Nova
adopt Glance v2 API. In this patch 'detail', 'download'
and 'delete' methods are improved to work with both versions.

Closes-bug: #1201266
Related to blueprint use-glance-v2-api

Change-Id: I9d89b2b265ba74e2a88007746ac09c6e5b80690a

[WIP] Glance v2 support in Nova

For testing purposes only.

Change-Id: Ic74815b74ca07929f88915c15810c0b917cf490f
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/nova refs/changes/40/316440/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: from glanceclient.v2 import schemas cfg.BoolOpt('use_glance_v1', default=False, """Provides storage and retrieval of disk image objects within Glance.""" def __init__(self, client=None): self._client = client or GlanceClientWrapper() # NOTE(jbresnah) build the table of download handlers at the beginning # so that operators can catch errors at load time rather than whenever # a user attempts to use a module. Note this cannot be done in glance # space when this python module is loaded because the download module # may require configuration options to be parsed. self._download_handlers = {} download_modules = image_xfers.load_transfer_modules() for scheme, mod in six.iteritems(download_modules): if scheme not in CONF.glance.allowed_direct_url_schemes: continue try: self._download_handlers[scheme] = mod.get_download_handler() except Exception as ex: LOG.error(_LE('When loading the module %(module_str)s the ' 'following error occurred: %(ex)s'), {'module_str': str(mod), 'ex': ex}) def detail(self, context, **kwargs): """Calls out to Glance for a list of detailed image information.""" params = _extract_query_params_v2(kwargs) try: images = self._client.call(context, 1, 'list', **params) except Exception: _reraise_translated_exception() _images = [] for image in images: if _is_image_available(context, image): _images.append(_translate_from_glance(image)) return _images def show(self, context, image_id, include_locations=False, show_deleted=True): """Returns a dict with image data for the given opaque image id. :param context: The context object to pass to image client :param image_id: The UUID of the image :param include_locations: (Optional) include locations in the returned dict of information if the image service API supports it. If the image service API does not support the locations attribute, it will still be included in the returned dict, as an empty list. :param show_deleted: (Optional) show the image even the status of image is deleted. """ try: image = self._client.call(context, 2, 'get', image_id) except Exception: _reraise_translated_image_exception(image_id) if not show_deleted and getattr(image, 'deleted', False): raise exception.ImageNotFound(image_id=image_id) if not _is_image_available(context, image): raise exception.ImageNotFound(image_id=image_id) image = _translate_from_glance(image, include_locations=include_locations) if include_locations: locations = image.get('locations', None) or [] du = image.get('direct_url', None) if du: locations.append({'url': du, 'metadata': {}}) image['locations'] = locations return image def _get_transfer_module(self, scheme): try: return self._download_handlers[scheme] except KeyError: return None except Exception: LOG.error(_LE("Failed to instantiate the download handler " "for %(scheme)s"), {'scheme': scheme}) return def download(self, context, image_id, data=None, dst_path=None): """Calls out to Glance for data and writes data.""" if CONF.glance.allowed_direct_url_schemes and dst_path is not None: image = self.show(context, image_id, include_locations=True) for entry in image.get('locations', []): loc_url = entry['url'] loc_meta = entry['metadata'] o = urlparse.urlparse(loc_url) xfer_mod = self._get_transfer_module(o.scheme) if xfer_mod: try: xfer_mod.download(context, o, dst_path, loc_meta) LOG.info(_LI("Successfully transferred " "using %s"), o.scheme) return except Exception: LOG.exception(_LE("Download image error")) try: image_chunks = self._client.call(context, 2, 'data', image_id) except Exception: _reraise_translated_image_exception(image_id) # Retrieve properties for verification of Glance image signature verifier = None if CONF.glance.verify_glance_signatures: image_meta_dict = self.show(context, image_id, include_locations=False) image_meta = objects.ImageMeta.from_dict(image_meta_dict) img_signature = image_meta.properties.get('img_signature') img_sig_hash_method = image_meta.properties.get( 'img_signature_hash_method' ) img_sig_cert_uuid = image_meta.properties.get( 'img_signature_certificate_uuid' ) img_sig_key_type = image_meta.properties.get( 'img_signature_key_type' ) try: verifier = signature_utils.get_verifier(context, img_sig_cert_uuid, img_sig_hash_method, img_signature, img_sig_key_type) except exception.SignatureVerificationError: with excutils.save_and_reraise_exception(): LOG.error(_LE('Image signature verification failed ' 'for image: %s'), image_id) close_file = False if data is None and dst_path: data = open(dst_path, 'wb') close_file = True if data is None: # Perform image signature verification if verifier: try: for chunk in image_chunks: verifier.update(chunk) verifier.verify() LOG.info(_LI('Image signature verification succeeded ' 'for image: %s'), image_id) except cryptography.exceptions.InvalidSignature: with excutils.save_and_reraise_exception(): LOG.error(_LE('Image signature verification failed ' 'for image: %s'), image_id) return image_chunks else: try: for chunk in image_chunks: if verifier: verifier.update(chunk) data.write(chunk) if verifier: verifier.verify() LOG.info(_LI('Image signature verification succeeded ' 'for image %s'), image_id) except cryptography.exceptions.InvalidSignature: data.truncate(0) with excutils.save_and_reraise_exception(): LOG.error(_LE('Image signature verification failed ' 'for image: %s'), image_id) except Exception as ex: with excutils.save_and_reraise_exception(): LOG.error(_LE("Error writing to %(path)s: %(exception)s"), {'path': dst_path, 'exception': ex}) finally: if close_file: data.close() def create(self, context, image_meta, data=None): """Store the image data and return the new image object.""" # Here we workaround the situation when user wants to activate an # empty image right after the creation. In Glance v1 api (and # therefore in Nova) it is enough to set 'size = 0'. v2 api # doesn't allow this hack - we have to send an upload request with # empty data. force_activate = data is None and image_meta.get('size') == 0 sent_service_image_meta = _translate_to_glance(image_meta) try: recv_service_image_meta = self._create_v2( context, sent_service_image_meta, data, force_activate) except glanceclient.exc.HTTPException: _reraise_translated_exception() return _translate_from_glance(recv_service_image_meta) def _add_location(self, context, image_id, location): # 'show_multiple_locations' must be enabled in glance api conf file. return self._client.call(context, 2, 'add_location', image_id, location, {}) def _upload_data(self, context, image_id, data): self._client.call(context, 2, 'upload', image_id, data) return self._client.call(context, 2, 'get', image_id) def _create_v2(self, context, sent_service_image_meta, data=None, force_activate=False): # Glance v1 allows image activation without setting disk and # container formats, v2 doesn't. It leads to the dirtiest workaround # where we have to hardcode this parameters. if force_activate: data = '' if 'disk_format' not in sent_service_image_meta: sent_service_image_meta['disk_format'] = 'qcow2' if 'container_format' not in sent_service_image_meta: sent_service_image_meta['container_format'] = 'bare' location = sent_service_image_meta.pop('location', None) recv_service_image_meta = self._client.call( context, 2, 'create', **sent_service_image_meta) # Sending image location in a separate request. if location: recv_service_image_meta = self._add_location( context, recv_service_image_meta['id'], location) # If we have some data we have to send it in separate request and # update 'recv_service_image_meta' then. if data is not None: recv_service_image_meta = self._upload_data( context, recv_service_image_meta['id'], data) return recv_service_image_meta def update(self, context, image_id, image_meta, data=None, purge_props=True): """Modify the given image with the new data.""" sent_service_image_meta = _translate_to_glance(image_meta) # NOTE(bcwaldon): id is not an editable field, but it is likely to be # passed in by calling code. Let's be nice and ignore it. sent_service_image_meta.pop('id', None) sent_service_image_meta['image_id'] = image_id try: if purge_props: # In Glance v2 we have to explicitly set prop names # we want to remove. all_props = set(self.show( context, image_id)['properties'].keys()) props_to_update = set( image_meta.get('properties', {}).keys()) remove_props = list(all_props - props_to_update) sent_service_image_meta['remove_props'] = remove_props recv_service_image_meta = self._update_v2( context, sent_service_image_meta, data) except Exception: _reraise_translated_image_exception(image_id) return _translate_from_glance(recv_service_image_meta) def _update_v2(self, context, sent_service_image_meta, data=None): location = sent_service_image_meta.pop('location', None) recv_service_image_meta = self._client.call( context, None, 'update', **sent_service_image_meta) # Sending image location in a separate request. if location: recv_service_image_meta = self._add_location( context, sent_service_image_meta['image_id'], location) # If we have some data we have to send it in separate request and # update 'recv_service_image_meta' then. if data is not None: recv_service_image_meta = self._upload_data( context, sent_service_image_meta['image_id'], data) return recv_service_image_meta def delete(self, context, image_id): """Delete the given image. :raises: ImageNotFound if the image does not exist. :raises: NotAuthorized if the user is not an owner. :raises: ImageNotAuthorized if the user is not authorized. """ try: self._client.call(context, 2, 'delete', image_id) except glanceclient.exc.NotFound: raise exception.ImageNotFound(image_id=image_id) except glanceclient.exc.HTTPForbidden: raise exception.ImageNotAuthorized(image_id=image_id) return True # TODO(mfedosin): Remove this function once we move to glance V2 # completely.def _extract_query_params_v2(params): _params = {} accepted_params = ('filters', 'marker', 'limit', 'page_size', 'sort_key', 'sort_dir') for param in accepted_params: if params.get(param): _params[param] = params.get(param) # ensure filters is a dict _params.setdefault('filters', {}) # NOTE(vish): don't filter out private images _params['filters'].setdefault('is_public', 'none') # adopt filters to be accepted by glance v2 api filters = _params['filters'] new_filters = {} for filter_ in filters: # remove 'property-' prefix from filters by custom properties if filter_.startswith('property-'): new_filters[filter_.lstrip('property-')] = filters[filter_] elif filter_ == 'changes-since': # convert old 'changes-since' into new 'updated_at' filter updated_at = 'gte:' + filters['changes-since'] new_filters['updated_at'] = updated_at elif filter_ == 'is_public': # convert old 'is_public' flag into 'visibility' filter # omit the filter if is_public is None is_public = filters['is_public'] if is_public.lower() in ('true', '1'): new_filters['visibility'] = 'public' elif is_public.lower() in ('false', '0'): new_filters['visibility'] = 'private' else: new_filters[filter_] = filters[filter_] _params['filters'] = new_filters return _params # TODO(mfedosin): Remove this check once we move to glance V2 # completely and enable convert to v2 every time. if not CONF.use_glance_v1: # v2 requires several additional changes image_meta = _convert_to_v2(image_meta)def _convert_to_v2(image_meta): output = {} for name, value in six.iteritems(image_meta): if name == 'properties': for prop_name, prop_value in six.iteritems(value): output[prop_name] = str(prop_value) elif name in ('min_ram', 'min_disk'): output[name] = int(value) elif name == 'is_public': output['visibility'] = 'public' if value else 'private' elif name == 'size' or name == 'deleted': continue elif name in ('kernel_id', 'ramdisk_id') and value == 'None': output[name] = None else: output[name] = value return output def _translate_from_glance(image, include_locations=False): # TODO(mfedosin): Remove this check once we move to glance V2 # completely. if CONF.use_glance_v1: image_meta = _extract_attributes( image, include_locations=include_locations) else: image_meta = _extract_attributes_v2( image, include_locations=include_locations) # TODO(mfedosin): Remove this function once we move to glance V2 # completely.def _extract_attributes_v2(image, include_locations=False): include_locations_attrs = ['direct_url', 'locations'] omit_attrs = ['self', 'schema', 'protected', 'virtual_size', 'file', 'tags'] raw_schema = image.schema schema = schemas.Schema(raw_schema) output = {'properties': {}, 'deleted': False, 'deleted_at': None} for name, value in six.iteritems(image): if (name in omit_attrs or name in include_locations_attrs and not include_locations): continue elif name == 'visibility': output['is_public'] = value == 'public' elif name == 'size' and value is None: output['size'] = 0 elif schema.is_base_property(name): output[name] = value else: output['properties'][name] = value return output

commit_message:
gpfs: Add changed options for 'find' command in rootwrap filters

Recently the 'find' command has been changed in gpfs driver
with a commit with change ID Id26cb59d88082971465c8fcf0c150c858ab3bced.
Adding the changed options in the rootwrap filters.

Change-Id: I3fde14949db57f89d7fa5e265a67d1d2d7884053
Closes-bug: 1581670
(cherry picked from commit b48614f2485c26f020781f815918ff198690e6a9)

added_lines: # Copyright (c) 2016 Mirantis, Inc. # # Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License"); you may # not use this file except in compliance with the License. You may obtain # a copy of the License at # # http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 # # Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software # distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS, WITHOUT # WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied. See the # License for the specific language governing permissions and limitations # under the License. """Simple Database API for all artifact types""" import uuid from oslo_log import log as logging import glance.common.glare.exception as glare_exc from glance.common import timeutils from glance.db.glare import api LOG = logging.getLogger(__name__) DATA = { 'artifacts': {} } def error_handler(f): def new_function(*args, **kwargs): try: return f(*args, **kwargs) except KeyError: raise glare_exc.NotFound() return new_function class SimpleAPI(api.BaseDBAPI): @error_handler def create(self, context, values): global DATA artifact_id = values.get('id', str(uuid.uuid4())) if artifact_id in DATA['artifacts']: raise glare_exc.BadRequest( "Artifact with id '%s' already exists" % artifact_id) if 'status' not in values: raise glare_exc.BadRequest("Status is a required attribute") values['created_at'] = values['updated_at'] = timeutils.utcnow() # values['owner'] = context.owner values['id'] = artifact_id values.setdefault('tags', []) values.setdefault('metadata', {}) DATA['artifacts'][artifact_id] = values return values @error_handler def update(self, context, artifact_id, values): global DATA af = DATA['artifacts'][artifact_id] af.update(values) DATA['artifacts'][artifact_id] = af return af @error_handler def delete(self, context, artifact_id): global DATA del DATA['artifacts'][artifact_id] @error_handler def get(self, context, artifact_id): global DATA return DATA['artifacts'][artifact_id] @error_handler def list(self, context, filters, marker, limit, sort): global DATA return DATA['artifacts'].values() @error_handler def add_tag(self, context, artifact_id, tag_value): global DATA DATA['artifacts'][artifact_id]['tags'].append(tag_value) return DATA['artifacts'][artifact_id]['tags'] @error_handler def remove_tag(self, context, artifact_id, tag_value): global DATA DATA['artifacts'][artifact_id]['tags'].remove(tag_value) return DATA['artifacts'][artifact_id]['tags'] @error_handler def get_tags(self, context, artifact_id): global DATA return DATA['artifacts'][artifact_id]['tags'] @error_handler def set_tags(self, context, artifact_id, tag_list): global DATA DATA['artifacts'][artifact_id]['tags'] = tag_list return DATA['artifacts'][artifact_id]['tags'] @error_handler def delete_tags(self, context, artifact_id): global DATA DATA['artifacts'][artifact_id]['tags'] = [] return DATA['artifacts'][artifact_id]['tags']

commit_message:
Tests fail silently when curl is not installed

If curl program is not installed, the script prepare_nailgun.sh
will fail in the fuel-client tests without giving any message.
This commit will add the reason why the test failed.

Change-Id: I747beefc2747e0fc8e5e4c87cf9561796585de96
Closes-Bug: #1566250

commit_message:
Require auth for version api call

The version call may contain information that should not be publicly
discloused without authentication. This change removes the version call
from the public urls which will cause it to require authentication
before responding with version information.

Change-Id: I7352f83ec67321a1fb5caa75fc9168cc01229083
Closes-Bug: #1585137

commit_message:
Let setup.py compile_catalog process all language files

Two years ago the translation files have been split into several
files, separating the log messages of different log levels from each
other, like X.pot, X-log-warning.pot, X-log-info.pot, and so on.
However, the setup.py command `compile_catalogs`, that comes from the
babel package and compiles the corresponding .po files into .mo
files, only supported one file per python package.  This means that
during packaging `compile_catalogs` never compiled the X-log-*.po
files, so the corresponding translations were always missing.

Since babel 2.3 the domain can be set to a space separated list of
domains.  This change adds the the additional log level files to the
domain list.

The obsolete check that .po and .pot files are valid is removed from
tox.ini.

Change-Id: I1f0bfb181e2b84ac6dd0ce61881cd2cc4400bdcb
Closes-Bug: #1536226

commit_message:
Support error handling for "port delete" command

"Port delete" command supported deleting multi ports
before but didn't support error handing, This patch
add the error handling following the rules in
doc/source/command-errors.rst.

Change-Id: I4ea69f2279763626d6a27cad1ca0ee99822d016d
Partially-Implements: blueprint multi-argument-network

commit_message:
update corresponding filter cases caused by output changed

Since the LOG.output translates the message is delayed to be
handled by logging code, so the message got from mock_log.
call_args is not translated. we should force translating it
beforce assertIn.

commit_message:
Change the default Fuel's Keystone token expiration

The amount of time a token remains valid should be decreased to
reduce potential security risks. This commit changes the defaults
to 6 hours. Also, this commit contains some styling cleanups.

Change-Id: I8563f89a1165d1f423ef59a86fab0f95a8444a25

commit_message:
Remove hardcoding namespaces for monitors

This patchset removes the need of hardcoding the monitor
namespaces inside the monitor init code.

The monitor namespaces are derived from the CONF options for
monitors instead. This allows us to not hardcode anything in
the monitor init code while new monitors are added.

Related to blueprint memory-bw

Change-Id: I37cd2d6850801999887b9f5a1ed7245a5f0618cc

CPU distribution mechanism should be changed due
to incorect requirements to nova and dpdk CPUs allocation

Changes:
 * Change CPU distribution
 * Add function for recognizing DPDK NICs for node
 * Remove requirement of enabled hugepages for
   DPDK NICs (it's checked before deployment)
 * Change HugePages distribution. Now it take into
   account Nova CPUs placement

Requirements Before:
 DPDK's CPUs should be located on the same NUMAs as
 Nova CPUs

Requirements Now:
 1. DPDK component CPU pinning has two parts:
     * OVS pmd core CPUs - These CPUs must be placed on the
       NUMAs where DPDK NIC is located. Since DPDK NIC can
       handle about 12 Mpps/s and 1 CPU can handle about
       3 Mpps/s there is no necessity to place more than
       4 CPUs per NIC. Let's name all remained CPUs as
       additional CPUs.
     * OVS Core CPUs - 1 CPU is enough and that CPU should
       be taken from any NUMA where at least 1 OVS pmd core
       CPU is located

 2. To improve Nova and DPDK performance, all additional CPUs
    should be distributed along with Nova's CPUs.

Change-Id: Ib2adf39c36b2e1536bb02b07fd8b5af50e3744b2
Closes-Bug: #1584006

commit_message:
Change CPU distribution

CPU distribution mechanism should be changed due
to incorect requirements to nova and dpdk CPUs allocation

Changes:
 * Change CPU distribution
 * Add function for recognizing DPDK NICs for node
 * Remove requirement of enabled hugepages for
   DPDK NICs (it's checked before deployment)
 * Change HugePages distribution. Now it take into
   account Nova CPUs placement

Requirements Before:
 DPDK's CPUs should be located on the same NUMAs as
 Nova CPUs

Requirements Now:
 1. DPDK component CPU pinning has two parts:
     * OVS pmd core CPUs - These CPUs must be placed on the
       NUMAs where DPDK NIC is located. Since DPDK NIC can
       handle about 12 Mpps/s and 1 CPU can handle about
       3 Mpps/s there is no necessity to place more than
       4 CPUs per NIC. Let's name all remained CPUs as
       additional CPUs.
     * OVS Core CPUs - 1 CPU is enough and that CPU should
       be taken from any NUMA where at least 1 OVS pmd core
       CPU is located

 2. To improve Nova and DPDK performance, all additional CPUs
    should be distributed along with Nova's CPUs as
    OVS pmd core CPUs.

Change-Id: Ib2adf39c36b2e1536bb02b07fd8b5af50e3744b2
Closes-Bug: #1584006

added_lines: # # Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License"); you may return bool(next(cls.dpdk_nics(node), None)) @classmethod def dpdk_nics_names(cls, transformations, bridge=None): """Returns generator with all NICs names based on transformations :param transformations: Fuel network transformations :type transformations: dict :param bridge: filter by bridge :type bridge: str :return: generator list[str] - names of DPDK NICs """ for t in transformations: action = t.get('action') name = t.get('name', '') provider = t.get('provider') if bridge and t.get('bridge') != bridge: continue if (action == 'add-port' and provider == consts.NEUTRON_L23_PROVIDERS.dpdkovs): yield name if (action == 'add-bond' and provider == consts.NEUTRON_L23_PROVIDERS.dpdkovs): for slave in t['interfaces']: yield slave @classmethod def dpdk_nics(cls, node): """Returns generator with dpdk interfaces :param node: Node SQLAlchemy model :type node: models.Node :return: generator list[models.NodeNICInterface] - DPDK NICs """ yield iface for bond in node.bond_interfaces: if objects.Bond.dpdk_enabled(bond): for slave in bond.slaves: yield slave def _node_template_transformations(cls, node): """Returns generator of node transformations by network template :param node: Node SQLAlchemy object :type node: models.Node :return: generator list[dict] - list transformations """ template_names = set() for role in node.all_roles: template_names.update( node.network_template['templates_for_node_role'][role]) templates = node.network_template['templates'] for tmpl_name in template_names: yield template[tmpl_name]['transformations'] @classmethod for transformation in cls._node_template_transformations(node): if next(cls.dpdk_nics_names( transformations, bridge=endpoint_name), None): return True @classmethod def dpdk_nics(cls, node): if node.network_template: transformations = cls._node_template_transformations(node) return [objects.NIC.get_nic_by_name(node, name) for name in cls.dpdk_nics_names(transformations)] else: return super(NeutronManager70, cls).dpdk_nics(node)
deleted_lines: # # Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License"); you may return True for iface in node.bond_interfaces: if objects.Bond.dpdk_enabled(iface): return True return False template_names = set() for role in node.all_roles: template_names.update( node.network_template['templates_for_node_role'][role]) templates = node.network_template['templates'] for tmpl_name in template_names: transformations = templates[tmpl_name]['transformations'] for t in transformations: if (t['action'] in ['add-port', 'add-bond'] and t.get('provider') == 'dpdkovs' and t.get('bridge') == endpoint_name): return True

subject: Don't overwrite ceph osd_journal_size
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-05-31 09:26:14.000000000', 'files': ['puppet/hieradata/ceph.yaml'], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/tripleo-heat-templates/commit/815ef9958d67e00925f13c5d23fc3898da9588e1', 'message': "Don't overwrite ceph osd_journal_size

The default journal size is 5 gigs. This change stops us
overwriting it with 1 gig that is too small for production.

The config value is used by ceph only when it creates the
journal so this does not affect upgrades.

commit_message:
Don't overwrite ceph osd_journal_size

The default journal size is 5 gigs. This change stops us
overwriting it with 1 gig that is too small for production.

The config value is used by ceph only when it creates the
journal so this does not affect upgrades.

Change-Id: I4bfd2ab47e131d8fcdd5dc75a5a56cfae8b22d5a

commit_message:
catch DriverLoadFailure for get_transport optional

new oslo.messaging 5.2.0 release will raise
oslo_messaging.transport.DriverLoadFailure if no existent transport
driver, hence breaks our code and unit test as well.

This patch fixes it by adding DriverLoadFailure to catch list.

Also:

tempest: import ImagesClient as ImagesClientV2

This commit [1] renamed ImagesClientV2 to ImagesClient so Ceilometer
Tempest tests do not work anymore.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/tempest/commit/2fea405bd6ea8674c8daaf8ebb788ae33d52c976

Change-Id: I02b5d1b3f4a9169cbf428a5eff9c6705494741af
Closes-Bug: #1588151
(cherry picked from commit d7f8ce94e433da8af3660ecf52715a04c221fde5)
(cherry picked from commit f6b2406fffdd4deae508b9f251691fe9b70cb1ee)

commit_message:
Save tempest accounts.yaml in logs

Some test jobs use pre-provisioned credentials. It can be useful
to have the credetials file for troubleshooting purposes, so copying
it to the logs folder when available.

commit_message:
[GATE UNBLOCKER] Lock CPU map script to a release

The CPU map script from devstack has been removed upstream.
This needs to be locked down to ensure we're not using the head
of master when depending on this script.

Upstream commit where the script was removed: [0].

To stablize the gate the script has been locked down using the a
SHA from the "stable/kilo" branch within upstream "devstack/tools" [1].

[0] - https://github.com/openstack-dev/devstack/commit/214459cdf776a77dacd70a9205c5b8a6ceaff31a
[1] - http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack-dev/devstack/plain/tools/cpu_map_update.py?h=a631abadde7346b49fab5b2ac16561dff77050d7

Change-Id: I0d55e799e4b4caff502438747fc65729dcaefd7e
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>
(cherry picked from commit 08ae3501d84d720a48c6c5a7fc0affa04b751d2e)

commit_message:
Add sanity tests for testing actions with Port

Smoke tests for the Ironic CLI commands
which checks basic actions with port command like
create, update, delete etc.

Change-Id: I1a1447d81c28af21b054e9cd4c35f94b39ac0244
Closes-Bug: #1527515
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/python-ironicclient refs/changes/44/240944/44 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: import random @staticmethod def generate_mac_address(): return ':'.join(random.choice('0123456789abcdef')*2 for x in range(6)) def _try_delete_port(self, port_id): port_list = self.list_port() if port_id in map(lambda item: item['UUID'], port_list): self.ironic('port-delete', params=port_id) port_list = self.list_port() port_list_uuid = map(lambda item: item['UUID'], port_list) if port_list in port_list_uuid: self.fail('Ironic port {0} has not been deleted!' .format(port_id)) def create_port(self, params=''): if not any(it in params for it in ('-a', '--address', '-n', '--node', '--node_uuid')): node = self.create_node() params += '--address {0} --node {1}'.format( self.generate_mac_address(), node['uuid']) port = self.ironic('port-create', params=params) port = self.get_dict_from_output(port) if not port.get('uuid'): self.fail('Ironic port has not been created!') self.addCleanup(self._try_delete_port, port['uuid']) return port def list_port(self, params=''): return self.ironic('port-list', params=params) def show_port(self, params): port_show = self.ironic('port-show', params=params) return self.get_dict_from_output(port_show)

commit_message:
Add Watcher docs and specs on openstack.org

As Watcher is now an official project,
documentation must be hosted on docs.openstack.org
and specifications generated on specs.openstack.org

Change-Id: I25cf9e6f4b2f4c2d9dacd1bcac7673f3524200c6

subject: Add Ironic Inspector discovery tempest job
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-06-06 12:58:54.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/project-config/commit/325e01b011ac16b9f12dbd7afd798c4f78be30c9', 'message': "Add Ironic Inspector extended tempest job

This patch adds new experimental job for running tempest with

commit_message:
[network] Improve neutron purge

This patch makes additions to the neutron purge page to clarify
that the command can be used with tenants that have been deleted
or otherwise do not exist in keystone.

It also documents the expected output when no supported resources
are found.

backport: mitaka
Co-Authored-By: Matt Kassawara <mkassawara@gmail.com>
Closes-Bug: 1580440
Change-Id: I562eb081630e124d690c27ae16d13f9793c5cafe
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/openstack-manuals refs/changes/12/321012/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: with a single command. This command can be used with any tenant ID, regardless of whether or not the tenant exists in the OpenStack Identity service. This is particularly useful for admins wishing to clean up resources belonging to deleted tenants. The following resources could not be deleted: 1 network. If no supported resources can be found that are associated with the given tenant ID, the command will return the following output: .. code-block:: console Tenant has no supported resources.
deleted_lines: with a single command. The following resouces could not be deleted: 1 network.

commit_message:
Update docs for latest VMware interoperability

* Minimum vCenter version should be 5.1.0.
* The preferred command line is openstack not glance
* vmware_linked_clone is legacy in favor of img_linked_clone

Change-Id: Ib75355998d76e528a487fbcdc577662dd820179b
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/openstack-manuals refs/changes/27/325327/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: 5.1.0 and newer, runs VMware-based Linux and Windows images through a connection with a vCenter server.
deleted_lines: 4.1 update 1 and newer, runs VMware-based Linux and Windows images through a connection with a vCenter server or directly with an ESXi host.

commit_message:
[networking-guide] Change l3 ha config in dvr_ha_snat

The fix include:
1.In the guide, ha_confs_path is DevStack path, Neutron default
ha_confs_path is $state_path/ha_confs, we do not need to make
an extra directory store it.
2.Remove another two default configurations for ha vrrp.
3.Remove no longer exist conf router_delete_namespaces.
4.Change entrypoint name for OVSInterfaceDriver.

Change-Id: I9ff5fb538d1b69b0ad091fde6644e110607007ed
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/openstack-manuals refs/changes/34/319034/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: ha_confs_path = /var/lib/neutron/ha_confs

commit_message:
[network] Clean up address scopes section

Streamline introduction and first section. Fix grammar in intro section.
Fix text-wrapping. Add numbering to use case section.

Closes-bug: #1581455
backport: mitaka

Change-Id: Iecd8ae58d2387606fc619f359413825705087eb9
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/openstack-manuals refs/changes/47/317047/2 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: This page serves as an introduction to the address scopes feature of the OpenStack Networking service. The Basics ~~~~~~~~~~ Address scopes build from subnet pools. While subnet pools provide a mechanism for controlling the allocation of addresses to subnets, address scopes show where addresses can be routed, preventing the use of overlapping addresses in any two subnets. Because all addresses allocated in the address scope do not overlap, neutron routers do not NAT between your tenants' network and your external network. As long as the addresses within an address scope match, neutron performs simple routing between networks. Accessing address scopes ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ Address scopes can be created by anyone within a network. However, network administrators can create shared address scopes that can be accessed by all tenants.
deleted_lines: Address scopes have been made available since the Mitaka release. They build from subnet pools added in Kilo. While subnet pools provide a mechanism for controlling the allocation of addresses to subnets, address scopes provide a way to know where addresses are viable. Like subnet pools, they also prevent using overlapping addresses in any two subnets. Why you need them ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ With address scopes, OpenStack Networking knows where addresses can be routed essentially because all of the allocated addresses within the scope are non-overlapping and they are under the control of the address scope owner. You can set up the address scopes for tenants to pull addresses from. Then, since neutron routers understand address scopes, they will not NAT between these networks and your external network as long as the scopes match. They will just do simple routing. How it works ~~~~~~~~~~~~ Anyone can create an address scope. Admins can create shared address scopes seen by all tenants.

Fix import for pylxd > 0.19

commit_message:
Add network quotas support

Add the capability to get, update and reset
to default quotas in network service.

Change-Id: I3396e5ecac1379af927f0a99a3b0c4c995dcd283
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/shade refs/changes/44/319144/5 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: class TestNetworkQuotas(base.TestCase): def setUp(self): super(TestNetworkQuotas, self).setUp() self.cloud = operator_cloud(cloud='devstack-admin') if not self.cloud.has_service('volume'): self.skipTest('network service not supported by cloud') def test_quotas(self): '''Test quotas functionality''' quotas = self.cloud.get_network_quotas('demo') network = quotas['network'] self.cloud.set_network_quotas('demo', network=network + 1) self.assertEqual(network + 1, self.cloud.get_network_quotas('demo')['network'] ) self.cloud.delete_network_quotas('demo') self.assertEqual(network, self.cloud.get_network_quotas('demo')['network'] )

commit_message:
Add ability to remove members from endpoints and interfaces hashes

into network_scheme.

All subhashes into interfaces and endpoints may be overrided by nil
or empty string values.

+ tests

Closes-bug: #1588934
Change-Id: I271c17b6fa70cd975fa98a1aa4edd4d7042b0d21

commit_message:
[GATE UNBLOCKER] Lock CPU map script to a release

The CPU map script from devstack has been removed upstream.
This needs to be locked down to ensure we're not using the head
of master when depending on this script.

Upstream commit where the script was removed: [0].

To stablize the gate the script has been locked down using the a

commit_message:
Increase tempest baremetal deploy/unprovision timeouts

This patch increase deploy/unprovision timeouts for ironic grenade jobs.
Grenade job launches smoke tempest tests, that builds several instances in
parallel, as result deploy/unprovision timeout should be increased for them.

Closes-Bug: #1580994

Change-Id: Id2856f4366744b2fc187b86a4d0d1db1e4b7c964
Depends-On: Idd454b7dea2a6d37a6bc048132fc2b3765d37429

commit_message:
Add ability to remove members from endpoints and interfaces hashes

into network_scheme.

All subhashes into interfaces and endpoints may be overrided by nil
or empty string values.

+ tests

Closes-bug: #1588934
Change-Id: I271c17b6fa70cd975fa98a1aa4edd4d7042b0d21

commit_message:
Remove unused _get_file_size()

Since I404e43e2e6ffecb5131cdcc43df03b8da0e7f0f8 , _get_file_size() was
never used. So this patch removes it for the code cleanup.

Change-Id: I4d36c140a137f2a7a72315c6ab952d5ca4e414cc
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/tempest refs/changes/75/326175/2 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
deleted_lines: def _get_file_size(self, obj): """Analyze file-like object and attempt to determine its size. :param obj: file-like object, typically redirected from stdin. :retval The file's size or None if it cannot be determined. """ # For large images, we need to supply the size of the # image file. See LP Bugs #827660 and #845788. if hasattr(obj, 'seek') and hasattr(obj, 'tell'): try: obj.seek(0, os.SEEK_END) obj_size = obj.tell() obj.seek(0) return obj_size except IOError as e: if e.errno == errno.ESPIPE: # Illegal seek. This means the user is trying # to pipe image data to the client, e.g. # echo testdata | bin/glance add blah..., or # that stdin is empty, or that a file-like # object which doesn't support 'seek/tell' has # been supplied. return None else: raise else: # Cannot determine size of input image return None

commit_message:
Import os-http into openstack infrastructure

os-http is a CLI for making raw http requests against OpenStack services
for development purposes. It handles the standard authentication and
discovery process so that you can focus on the response.

Change-Id: I2767bdc395f686199fa6547dc9229b5c2b2711b1

'}, {'number': 7, 'created': '2016-02-09 09:38:37.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/neutron-lbaas/commit/fef9f6e44963ddc28648be8dc8ff93fea44cb5ca', 'message': 'Get Me A LB

Allows a request to be passed to the lbaas API that contains the full graph
structure of a load balancer.  This means that an entire load balancer graph
can be created in one POST to the API, or a partial graph can be.

This creates a new driver method to the driver interface that when implemented
will be called when a full or partial graph is attempted to be created.  If
the driver does not implement this method, then the request is not allowed.

Closes-Bug: #1463202
Depends-On: Id3a5ddb8efded8c6ad72a7118424ec01c777318d
Change-Id: Ic16ca4cb3cb407d9e91eea74315a39bf86c654f3

commit_message:
Get Me A LB

Allows a request to be passed to the lbaas API that contains the full graph
structure of a load balancer.  This means that an entire load balancer graph
can be created in one POST to the API, or a partial graph can be.

This creates a new driver method to the driver interface that when implemented
will be called when a full or partial graph is attempted to be created.  If
the driver does not implement this method, then the request is not allowed.

Co-Author: Trevor Vardeman <trevor.vardeman@rackspace.com>

Closes-Bug: #1463202
Depends-On: Id3a5ddb8efded8c6ad72a7118424ec01c777318d
Change-Id: Ic16ca4cb3cb407d9e91eea74315a39bf86c654f3

added_lines: def create_loadbalancer_tree(self, context, loadbalancer, allocate_vip=True): with context.session.begin(subtransactions=True): lb_db = self.create_loadbalancer(context, loadbalancer, allocate_vip=allocate_vip) for listener in loadbalancer.get('listeners', []): default_pool = listener.pop('default_pool', None) if default_pool: hm = default_pool.pop('healthmonitor', None) if hm: hm_db = self.create_healthmonitor(context, hm) default_pool['healthmonitor_id'] = hm_db.id members = default_pool.pop('members', []) pool_db = self.create_pool(context, listener.get('default_pool')) listener['default_pool_id'] = pool_db.id for member in members: member['pool_id'] = pool_db.id self.create_pool_member(context, member) self.create_listener(context, listener) return data_models.LoadBalancer.from_sqlalchemy_model(lb_db)

commit_message:
Revert "Migrate tripleo to centos-7"

This reverts commit 791021c4b902b84ecabce30fa223039cd69b5948.

We tried this migration today and seem to be having a variety of
job failures and timeouts ever since. Lets revert for now to fix
CI and then we can perhaps try to switch back once we've done
more Centos 7 testing.

Change-Id: I83a2de65b624ded850a974a18c532b470a1ec97c

- Update noop tests

commit_message:
Fix the broken amqp version

The amqp 2.0 is not backwards compatible with kombu driver of
oslo.messaging. All functional tests of kombu driver are fails with:
AttributeError: 'Connection' object has no attribute '_frame_writer'

Closes-Bug: #1586840

Change-Id: If7e130a70f31a2eb1d9df6b5f46f88c90880e254

commit_message:
Using LOG.warning instead of LOG.warn

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning
so we prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

Change-Id: Iac71d0c6d4209c236f4a4149eec0d08ec1682271

commit_message:
Move _format_volume_id() outside of take_action() method in VolumeV2

There are two reasons to move it:
1.To keep consistent with other commands.
2.We need to call _format_volume_id() method in unit test,so we
should not let it in the take_action() method.

Change-Id: I98fee5e416fa55c1c6ddddb466342f972d611a14

commit_message:
Storwize: terminate_connetion NPIV perf improvement

When terminate connection is called on a VM that is using
NPIV connections while the VM is shutdown such as when the
the VM is being deleted, the NPIV ports are no longer logged
into the fabric and the lsfabric fast path will not find the VM.
Add a fast path this NPIV case is to first check the host names
from the list of hosts that have mapped the volume before
exhaustively searching the entire host list for a match

Fixed an issue with the simulator not resetting lshost after
the simulated condition fired.

Added a new UT to cover the code change.

Change-Id: Ie38fb708ad7eae62261e71ab0bcb505c3efdb3b1
Closes-Bug: #1580342

commit_message:
Fix errors for "volume type unset" command

Normally, we can unset multi properties but the "volume type unset"
command could not, because the action "append" was missed. So I add
it and also fix the unit test and doc in this patch.

Change-Id: I20470f2b7bb2a8d7f292cea498826669c3418c77

commit_message:
Fix required_api_versions validator

This makes two changes:

* When the validator is configured to require either Keystone v2.0 or
  Keystone v3, it actually works now. Before that made it always fail.
* The validator attempts to read component versions from context;
  otherwise it was impossible to run a non-Keystone scnario with a
  required version on a cluster with multiple API versions
  enabled. (E.g., you couldn't require Glance v2 for a scenario and
  run it on a cluster with both Glance v1 and v2 enabled.)

Test coverage is also expanded and tests are reorganized.

Change-Id: I996f789a86e6e74562fe8b3b1eab60b67b0b9fa7

commit_message:
Check which glance client version to use

Nova is working toward supporting the glance v2 API which will
allow disabling the glance v1 API in glance in a deployment and
configuring Nova to only use the glance v2 API.

The existing API and scenario tests are setting up a base test image
using the glance v1 client regardless of whether or not the glance v1
API is enabled in tempest.conf.

This adds a check to the tests to see which glance client version
to use depending on the config.

Change-Id: I1b1dc2911698d4e4d1a2727902ba457688d88752
Closes-Bug: #1589093

added_lines: # Check if glance v1 is available to determine which client to use. We # prefer glance v1 for the compute API tests since the compute image # API proxy was written for glance v1. if CONF.image_feature_enabled.api_v1: cls.glance_client = cls.os.image_client elif CONF.image_feature_enabled.api_v2: cls.glance_client = cls.os.image_client_v2 else: skip_msg = ('%s skipped as glance v1 nor glance v2 is available' % cls.__name__) raise cls.skipException(skip_msg)

commit_message:
objects: support advanced criteria for get_objects

Those are needed to accommodate to API request needs without handling
sorting or pagination in Python.

Instead of adding four new arguments to get_objects interface, they are
consolidated using a single Pager object that is passed through the
_pager argument. The name uses underscore to avoid breaking objects that
want to pass 'pager' filter into SQLAlchemy. Hopefully, no objects will
ever have '_pager' attribute in their models.

Related-Bug: #1541928
Change-Id: I7dafc4dbd80f0ac35dbc2c2f30e56e441f5b1fc0

commit_message:
remove neutron stuff from devstack deb packages

It seems we are enforcing certain dependencies to be always installed on
behalf of other projects.  The issue I'm facing is we unconditionally
install openvswitch-datapath-dkms which isn't necessary for Ubuntu kernels
>= 3.13.  Even worse, this package isn't available on Ubuntu 16.4 LTS thus
breaking devstack setup.sh on that platform.

This patch removes Neutron dependencies as those are handled by devstack[1]
and devstack neutron plugin[2]

[1] https://github.com/openstack-dev/devstack/blob/master/files/debs/openvswitch#L3
[2] https://github.com/openstack-dev/devstack/blob/master/lib/neutron_plugins/ovs_base#L58

Closes-bug: #1580101

Change-Id: Iff0cf13499d9cb05f241f23759d5faec9a9c4a98

commit_message:
Switch to using correct TaskFlow Failure class

Our manage_existing_snapshot code was checking for failure by
checking if the result was a taskflow.utils.misc.Failure instance.
This class was deprecated some time ago and has now been removed
in the latest 2.0 TaskFlow release with TaskFlow
commit afbfe77a7f7bad87c3e95b4f0c94cab84258a5bb.

Switched over to using the newer and correct
taskflow.types.failure.Failure class.

Change-Id: I0f427b31ce25e4991ba7c32e65cb56ed575ea20d
Closes-bug: #1588584

commit_message:
Add equality operator to policy.RuleDefault

There are occasions when comparing two RuleDefault objects is needed.
Rather than embedding the logic at the comparison site it's preferable
to let the object know how to compare itself to another.

Change-Id: I2eae5665fdecd6638e84f577b506314f7bc03fd3

commit_message:
a depth in `get topology show` API can only be used
if there is a root

using vitrage in env without any root graph, unable to request
topology of type graph. A depth in `get topology show` API can
only be used if there is a root.

Change-Id: I4267037748f09e08ad3a3de76367ec5c8f055e8c
Fixes: bug #1586249
Signed-off-by: dongwenjuan <dong.wenjuan@zte.com.cn>

commit_message:
refactor keystone_user, keystone_user_role providers

When domain_specific_drivers are enabled in keystone
'--domain' option is mandatory when requesting 'user list'

Change-Id: Ic8aed7cce488a78dbc4fb5d461400cc59dc8589a
Closes-Bug: #1485508
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/puppet-keystone refs/changes/06/213906/2 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: domain_hash.keys.collect do |domain| request('user', 'list', ['--long', '--domain', "#{domain}"] ).each do |user| # The field says "domain" but it is really the domain_id domname = domain_name_from_id(user[:domain]) if instance_hash.include?(user[:name]) # not unique curdomid = instance_hash[user[:name]][:domain] if curdomid != default_domain_id # Move the user from the short name slot to the long name slot # because it is not in the default domain. curdomname = domain_name_from_id(curdomid) instance_hash["#{user[:name]}::#{curdomname}"] = instance_hash[user[:name]] # Use the short name slot for the new user instance_hash[user[:name]] = user else # Use the long name for the new user instance_hash["#{user[:name]}::#{domname}"] = user end # Unique (for now) - store in short name slot instance_hash[user[:name]] = user
deleted_lines: request('user', 'list', ['--long']).each do |user| # The field says "domain" but it is really the domain_id domname = domain_name_from_id(user[:domain]) if instance_hash.include?(user[:name]) # not unique curdomid = instance_hash[user[:name]][:domain] if curdomid != default_domain_id # Move the user from the short name slot to the long name slot # because it is not in the default domain. curdomname = domain_name_from_id(curdomid) instance_hash["#{user[:name]}::#{curdomname}"] = instance_hash[user[:name]] # Use the short name slot for the new user instance_hash[user[:name]] = user # Use the long name for the new user instance_hash["#{user[:name]}::#{domname}"] = user else # Unique (for now) - store in short name slot instance_hash[user[:name]] = user

commit_message:
Fix Ceilometer tests config options

Ceilometer tempest tests have been moved to plugin but config options
were renamed as same were registered by Tempest also.

Now Tempest is removing ceilometer tests and related config options
- I0775bcc15dc9cbae6e075fe92f44b5f6c9b9d5d2
we need to fix their name back to original one to avoid backward incompatibility.

Congress use those in ceilometer integration tests and will break if we
do not rename those back to original one.

Change-Id: Id10cd260d12eba5b4f4d7798dee64fc62a92eb1c
Depends-On: I0775bcc15dc9cbae6e075fe92f44b5f6c9b9d5d2

added_lines: =============================== Neutron Dynamic Routing Drivers =============================== Introduction ============ The neutron dynamic routing drivers are used to configure different dynamic routing protocol stacks which implement the BGP functionality. As shown in the following figure, the drivers are managed by DRAgent through "Driver Manager", the driver manager controls a common driver API which provides a consistent interface for different dynamic routing protocol stack drivers. In the first release, we only deliver codes for the Ryu driver, we will add Quagga driver in future release:: Neutron Dynamic Routing Drivers +-------------------------------+ | DRAgent | | | | +-------------------------+ | | | Driver Manager | | | +-------------------------+ | | | Common Driver API | | | +-------------------------+ | | | | | | | | +------------+------------+ | | | Ryu | Other | | | | Driver | Drivers | | | +------------+------------+ | | | +-------------------------------+ Driver Configurations ===================== There are two parameters related with driver in dynamic routing configuration file bgp_dragent.ini: * bgp_speaker_driver BGP speaker driver class to be instantiated, default is Ryu driver class neutron_dynamic_routing.services.bgp.agent.driver.ryu.driver.RyuBgpDriver, you can change it to other driver class if you like. * bgp_router_id BGP identifier, typically an IPv4 address. The default is loopback IP address 127.0.0.1, it must be unique in the network, you can change it if need. Common Driver API ================= A common Driver API is needed to provide a generic and consistent interface for different dynamic routing protocol drivers. Each driver need implement it in the driver class. The following table shows all the common driver APIs. +--------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+ |API name |Description | +================================+=========================================+ |add_bgp_speaker() |Add a BGP Speaker | +--------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+ |delete_bgp_speaker() |Delete a BGP speaker | +--------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+ |add_bgp_peer() |Add a BGP peer | +--------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+ |delete_bgp_peer() |Delete a BGP peer | +--------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+ |advertise_route() |Add a new prefix to advertise | +--------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+ |withdraw_route() |Withdraw an advertised prefix | +--------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+ |get_bgp_speaker_statistics() |Collect BGP Speaker statistics | +--------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+ |get_bgp_peer_statistics() |Collect BGP Peer statistics | +--------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+

added_lines: ======================= Neutron Dynamic Routing ======================= Introduction ============ Neutron dynamic routing enables advertisement of self-service (private) network prefixes to physical network devices that support dynamic routing protocols such as routers, thus removing the conventional dependency on static routes. It advertises three classes of routes: * Host routes for floating IP addresses hosted on non-DVR routers, the nexthop is the centralized router * Host routes for floating IP addresses hosted on DVR routers, the nexthop is the appropriate compute node * Prefix routes for directly routable tenant networks with address scopes, the nexthop is the centralized router Neutron dynamic routing consists of a service plug-in and an agent. The service plug-in implements the Networking service extension and the agent manages dynamic routing protocol peering sessions. There are many kinds of dynamic routing protocols, only BGP is supported in the first release, we can add other protocols in the future. System Architecture =================== The following figure shows the architecture of this feature. As shown in the diagram, BGP speaker can be automatically scheduled to one host running the dragent, through the "BGP DRAgentScheduler". Alternatively, administrator can manually schedule it to one or more hosts running the dragent. Dragents can reside on hosts with or without other Networking service agents, it manages and configures different dynamic routing stack through "Common Driver API", In the first release, we only deliver codes for the Ryu driver, we will add Quagga driver in future release. The plugin communicates with the agent through RPC:: Neutron dynamic Routing System Architecture +---------------------------------------------------------------+ | Neutron dynamic routing plugin | | +---------------------------------------------------------+ | | | BGP API | | | +---------------------------------------------------------+ | | | BGP Database | | | +---------------------------------------------------------+ | | | BGP Speaker | | | +---------------------------------------------------------+ | | | BGP DRAgentScheduler | | | +---------------------------------------------------------+ | | | | +------------------------------|--------------------------------+ | | +-----------+ | RPC | +-----------+ | | +----------------------|-------------------------+ | | | | +---------------------------+ +---------------------------+ | DR Agent1 | | DR Agent2 | | | | | | +---------------------+ | | +---------------------+ | | | Driver Manager | | | | Driver Manager | | | +---------------------+ | | +---------------------+ | | | Common Driver API | | | | Common Driver API | | | +---------------------+ | | +---------------------+ | | | | | | | | +---------+-----------+ | | +---------+-----------+ | | | Ryu | Other | | | | Ryu | Other | | | | Driver | Drivers | | | | Driver | Drivers | | | +---------+-----------+ | | +---------+-----------+ | | | | | +---------------------------+ +---------------------------+

commit_message:
Migrate to nova api version 2.1

The Nova v2 API code has been completely removed from Nova by
change[1]. Although Nova still supports v2 compatible API with the
legacy endpoint, it is better to switch to use Nova v2.1 in Heat.

This change sets version='2.1' when init novaclient
instance, then we can use novaclient v2 and will
use nova api v2.1.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/311653/

Change-Id: I428abb4ca05847da8ffc2da7157aa5c34263a205
Closes-Bug: #1588155
Partial-Bug: #1588171

commit_message:
Pure project admin can't view Projects page

With Domains enabled, if you create a Project, with a user
who is an admin on that project (but not a domain admin),
the Identity > Projects panel will return a 500 error.

commit_message:
Keystone uwsgi performance tuning

I ran some tests locally that showed that when using the uwsgi
deploy the keystone server wasn't using all the processes
available. When I switched from "threads" to "processes" the
concurrent performance improved considerably. So I'm proposing
that the docs use processes to improve performance.

Change-Id: I5375702f45ccb82c02ff2bba1eabda836d5d25eb

commit_message:
Make error message in modal a unified style

When the required field in a modal form leaved blank, all the error
message are in red only the asterisk is in blue. All the error
message should be in unified style.

Change-Id: I7aaffdb79f72173f39f53329ea5595f61f6ffecc
Closes-Bug: #1588136

commit_message:
Convergence: Fix unit tests

Some of the unit tests fail when convergence_engine is set as true
in config. This is mainly due to the convergence flag in some of the
functions/methods which is expected to be True but is set to False for
legacy engine.

Change-Id: I57ef37d4fd79f0b453aef9c16876495901c2d802
Closes-Bug: #1567321

commit_message:
Update tests to work with Ironic grenade

Smoke tests that can't work with Ironic due to design are skipped
when Ironic is enabled.
In case of Ironic after instace delete cleaning process is called.
We consider instance is deleted when:
 * Instance is disassociated from Ironic node.
 * Node is moved to available state.
 * Nova hypervisor fields are updated.
Add additional check wait_bm_node_unprovisioned after instance deleting
to wait for Ironic node to be in available state and hypervisor stats
are updated.

Change-Id: I15d23b474e4654d1ef513e6409399f44f088b5c5
Co-Authored-By: Vladyslav Drok (vdrok@mirantis.com)

commit_message:
Fixed tempest plugin

The plugin was broken by tempest
change I5a4523c20c19957bfccf2aa95157baf106b3d364. We can't blame tempest
here because we definitely referred to an internal symbol in tempest
tree.

Now we have a proper symbol from tempest.lib, so it should be safe to
use it.

(cherry picked from commit 73474780aa3ba094e8fe01ae33269b7ad43dc2b0)
Change-Id: I42812a949103679e2559f310bb95c597c368015f
Closes-Bug: #1589521

commit_message:
Allow to set Ironic provision timeout from the job

Launching smoke tempest tests building several instances in parallel.
As result grenade job that uses tempest smoke tests need to have
higher provision/unprovision timeout values value.
This patch allows to set BUILD_TIMEOUT from the job.

Change-Id: Idd454b7dea2a6d37a6bc048132fc2b3765d37429

commit_message:
Make the notifier max_workers configurable

Make the max_workers attribute of NotifierDriver configurable.
Now it can be configured using 'max_workers' parameter. Default
value of max_workers is 10.

Co-Authored-By: wangxiyuan<wangxiyuan@huawei.com>
Change-Id: Ice7d12199f8463793951932b48408e7df81440f2
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/zaqar refs/changes/43/308443/1 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: # Make the max_workers configurable, default value is 10 max_workers = kwargs.get('max_workers', 10) self.executor = futurist.ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=max_workers)
deleted_lines: # TODO(flwang): Make the max_workers configurable self.executor = futurist.ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=10)

added_lines: --- features: - The ``dib-lint`` tool now has a best-effort sudo check to help flag uses of ``sudo`` outside the chroot environment. This can help avoid some classes of breakout problems that can interfere with the host system. - Running with ``-x`` will give a more verbose log output that includes function and line-numbers. Work is ongoing to further reduce noise in the verbose logs to make it as useful as possible. Feedback is welcome on the new format. - the ``pkg-map`` element can now install different packages based on the distribution release. fixes: - Locale stripping for ``yum-minimal`` has been reworked to be more reliable for Fedora 23 and CentOS. - The Ubuntu Precise kernel is too old to use the online ``growroot`` element, so we returned to using ``cloud-initramfs-growroot`` in the ``debootstrap`` element for it. - The ``dib-lint`` tool now better matches python files. - The ``apt-sources`` element was fixed to work with the ``debian-minimal`` element. - Dependencies for the systemd target in ``dhcp-all-interfaces`` were updated to correctly wait for interfaces.

Add negative tempest API test for cluster update

This patch adds negative tempest API test for cluster
update API interface.

Change-Id: I33bf8b8ac01c5474318a90063c803fa619a1f106
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/senlin refs/changes/77/325777/2 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD

See the # License for the specific language governing permissions and limitations # under the License. import copy from tempest.lib import decorators from tempest.lib import exceptions from tempest import test from senlin.tests.tempest.api import base from senlin.tests.tempest.api import utils from senlin.tests.tempest.common import constants class TestClusterUpdateNegativeNotFound(base.BaseSenlinTest): @test.attr(type=['negative']) @decorators.idempotent_id('f7a97fce-f495-44a8-b41a-7408139adacf') def test_cluster_update_cluster_not_found(self): self.assertRaises(exceptions.NotFound, self.client.update_obj, 'clusters', 'f7a97fce-f495-44a8-b41a-7408139adacf', {'cluster': {'name': 'new-name'}}) class TestClusterUpdateNegativeBadRequest(base.BaseSenlinTest): def setUp(self): super(TestClusterUpdateNegativeBadRequest, self).setUp() # Create a profile profile_id = utils.create_a_profile(self) self.addCleanup(utils.delete_a_profile, self, profile_id) self.profile_id = profile_id # Create a cluster self.cluster_id = utils.create_a_cluster(self, profile_id) self.addCleanup(utils.delete_a_cluster, self, self.cluster_id) # Create a new profile of different type self.new_profile_id1 = utils.create_a_profile( self, spec=constants.spec_heat_stack) self.addCleanup(utils.delete_a_profile, self, self.new_profile_id1) # Create two new profiles of the same type with the same name new_spec = copy.deepcopy(constants.spec_nova_server) new_spec['properties']['flavor'] = 'new_flavor' new_profile_id2 = utils.create_a_profile(self, new_spec, name='p-nova') new_profile_id3 = utils.create_a_profile(self, new_spec, name='p-nova') self.addCleanup(utils.delete_a_profile, self, new_profile_id2) self.addCleanup(utils.delete_a_profile, self, new_profile_id3) @test.attr(type=['negative']) @decorators.idempotent_id('fb68921d-1fe8-4c14-be9a-51fa43d4f705') def test_cluster_update_bad_request_profile_not_found(self): # Provided profile can not be found params = { 'cluster': { 'profile_id': 'fb68921d-1fe8-4c14-be9a-51fa43d4f705', } } # Verify badrequest exception(400) is raised. self.assertRaises(exceptions.BadRequest, self.client.update_obj, 'clusters', self.cluster_id, params) @test.attr(type=['negative']) @decorators.idempotent_id('6a3eb86c-4b5c-4cfc-891c-7b0be17715f2') def test_cluster_update_bad_request_profile_multiple_choices(self): # Multiple profiles are found for given name params = { 'cluster': { 'profile_id': 'p-nova', } } # Verify badrequest exception(400) is raised. self.assertRaises(exceptions.BadRequest, self.client.update_obj, 'clusters', self.cluster_id, params) @test.attr(type=['negative']) @decorators.idempotent_id('c28e1bc0-fadb-4394-b2d0-67ad8b87ac04') def test_cluster_update_bad_request_profile_type_unmatch(self): # New profile type is different from original cone params = { 'cluster': { 'profile_id': self.new_profile_id1, } } # Verify badrequest exception(400) is raised. self.assertRaises(exceptions.BadRequest, self.client.update_obj, 'clusters', self.cluster_id, params)

commit_message:
Show 'age' field in subscriptions (redis)

We recently fixed subscriptions and now they are expirable resources as
they should be.

This patch adds 'age' field to subscription resource representation
which is exposed to the user and defined in redis driver.

This patch also removes existing 'expires' field, because:
1. The 'expires' field is missing in mongodb's subscription resource
representation. (But age field was also missing until a recent patch).
2. The 'expires' field has int (timestamp) format, which is not human
readable.
3. Other Zaqar's expirable resources show 'age' and 'ttl' fields instead
of showing 'expires' field.
4. There is no need in 'expires' field when 'age' and 'ttl' fields are
exposed to the user.

This change in unlikely to affect backward compatibility, because
subscription expirations started to work only recently.

Closes-Bug: 1552845
APIImpact
DocImpact
Change-Id: I18f908b2f137bd4b8e5b3d3275063a1d37942093

added_lines: now = timeutils.utcnow_ts() ttl = int(record[2]) expires = int(record[3]) created = expires - ttl 'ttl': ttl, 'age': now - created, 'options': self._unpacker(record[4]), now = timeutils.utcnow_ts() return subscription.to_basic(now)

commit_message:
Show 'age' field in subscriptions (mongodb)

We recently fixed subscriptions and now they are expirable resources as
they should be.
But now, unlike messages and claims, they don't show their age, so it's
impossible for the user to know when the particular subscription will
expire.

This patch adds 'age' field to subscription resource representation
returned from mongodb driver. Tests are modified to make them check also
'age' field.

Partial-Bug: 1552845
APIImpact
DocImpact

commit_message:
Cleanup source-repositories output

This element takes up a *huge* part of the logs of openstack-infra
builds as we go and cache every git tree.

This silences most of the noise which will reduce the mess
in the logs considerably.

Note that we've had logging on this turned down since
I91c5e55814ba9840769357261d203f4850e2eba6 but it has been
ineffective in stopping the log-spew output, see the
dependency change.

Change-Id: I60f06f84d57087c82b3907575bff125015d35171
Depends-On: I1e39822f218dc0322e2490a770f3dc867a55802c

added_lines: # this can be a rather long list (e.g. caching ~1000 openstack # repos), so we make a rough count for a progres local COUNT=0 local REPO_SOURCES_COUNT=$(grep -v '^$\|^\s*\#' $REPO_SOURCES | wc -l) # temporarily turn off globbing '*' (since it may be used as # the REPOREF for tarballs) and expand variables set -f; line=$(eval echo $line); set +f # rough progress counter printf "(%04d / %04d)\n" ${COUNT} ${REPO_SOURCES_COUNT} COUNT=$(( COUNT + 1)) git clone -q $REPOLOCATION $CACHE_PATH.tmp if [ "$REPOREF" == "*" ] || ! git --git-dir=$CACHE_PATH/.git fetch -q --prune --update-head-ok $REPOLOCATION \ git --git-dir=$CACHE_PATH/.git fetch -q --prune --update-head-ok $REPOLOCATION \ pushd $REPO_DEST > /dev/null popd > /dev/null sudo git clone -q $CACHE_PATH $REPO_DEST pushd $REPO_DEST > /dev/null sudo git fetch -q --prune --update-head-ok $CACHE_PATH \ sudo git fetch -q $CACHE_PATH $REPOREF:fetch_$REPOREF popd > /dev/null echo "$REPOPATH" | sudo tee -a $TMP_MOUNT_PATH/etc/dib-source-repositories > /dev/null
deleted_lines: # temporarily turn off globbing '*' (since it may be used as the REPOREF for tarballs) set -f # expand variables line=$(eval echo $line) # restore globbing set +f git clone $REPOLOCATION $CACHE_PATH.tmp if [ "$REPOREF" == "*" ] || ! git --git-dir=$CACHE_PATH/.git fetch --prune --update-head-ok $REPOLOCATION \ git --git-dir=$CACHE_PATH/.git fetch --prune --update-head-ok $REPOLOCATION \ pushd $REPO_DEST popd sudo git clone $CACHE_PATH $REPO_DEST pushd $REPO_DEST sudo git fetch --prune --update-head-ok $CACHE_PATH \ sudo git fetch $CACHE_PATH $REPOREF:fetch_$REPOREF popd echo "$REPOPATH" | sudo dd of=$TMP_MOUNT_PATH/etc/dib-source-repositories oflag=append conv=notrunc

[network] Add interface driver for LBaaS agent

This patch fix some errors in neutron lbaas v2 doc, and add the
configuration details towards setup lbaas v2 with an agent.

Closes-Bug: #1589404
backport: mitaka

commit_message:
Fix the bug that tox fail to run test_messaging

When conf of rpc_backend equal to none, invoking method of
oslo_messaging.get_transport will raise oslo_messaging.DriverLoadFailure.

Change-Id: I5bc1269732a463718cd9d1e38c1f10e691322794
Closes-Bug: #1589396

commit_message:
Create default mtu and default routes for switch and subnet

Make sure that if an mtu is not specified on an lswitch, then its value
is None, and make sure that if no host_routes were defined on a subnet,
then the value is the empty list.
